OL,3,CMan suffers third-degree burns after
OL,4,Cvape explodes in his pocket
OL,6,FWarning: This story contains graphic
OL,7,Fimages of burns
OL,9,FA man has told of the terrifying
OL,10,Fmoment his e-cigarette battery
OL,11,Fexploded in his pocket, saying "it
OL,12,Ffelt like my leg had been put in an
OL,13,Foven".
OL,15,FRobert Kane, 37, from Manchester, had
OL,16,Fto learn to walk again after the
OL,17,Fcorrosive battery acid ate through the
OL,18,Fskin on his thigh and lower leg.
